  "chapter": {
    "number": 45,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God Calls Cyrus"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This is what the LORD says to Cyrus His anointed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "whose right hand I have grasped",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to subdue nations before him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to disarm kings,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to open the doors before him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that the gates will not be shut:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I will go before you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and level the mountains;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2670
          },
          {
            "text": "I will break down the gates of bronze",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and cut through the bars of iron.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will give you the treasures of darkness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the riches hidden in secret places,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that you may know that I am the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the God of Israel, who calls you by name.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the sake of Jacob My servant",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Israel My chosen one,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I call you by name;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have given you a title of honor,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "though you have not known Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I am the LORD, and there is no other;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there is no God but Me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will equip you for battle,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "though you have not known Me,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "so that all may know,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from where the sun rises to where it sets,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that there is none but Me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I am the LORD, and there is no other.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I form the light and create the darkness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I bring prosperity and create calamity.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I, the LORD, do all these things.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drip down, O heavens, from above,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and let the skies pour down righteousness.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let the earth open up that salvation may sprout",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and righteousness spring up with it;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I, the LORD, have created it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to him who quarrels with his Maker—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "one clay pot among many.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Does the clay ask the potter,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘What are you making?’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2671
          },
          {
            "text": "Does your work say,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘He has no hands’?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to him who says to his father,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘What have you begotten?’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "or to his mother,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘What have you brought forth?’”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thus says the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Holy One of Israel, and its Maker:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“How dare you question Me about My sons,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or instruct Me in the work of My hands?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It is I who made the earth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and created man upon it.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "It was My hands that stretched out the heavens,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I ordained all their host.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will raise up Cyrus in righteousness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will make all his ways straight.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will rebuild My city",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and set My exiles free,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but not for payment or reward,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "says the LORD of Hosts.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "This is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“The products of Egypt and the merchandise of Cush,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2672
          },
          {
            "text": "along with the Sabeans, men of stature,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "will come over to you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and will be yours;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they will trudge behind you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will come over in chains and bow down to you.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will confess to you:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘God is indeed with you, and there is no other;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "there is no other God.’”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Truly You are a God who hides Himself,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O God of Israel, the Savior.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will all be put to shame and humiliated;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the makers of idols will depart together in disgrace.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But Israel will be saved by the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with an everlasting salvation;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you will not be put to shame or humiliated,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to ages everlasting.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For thus says the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who created the heavens—He is God;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He formed the earth and fashioned it;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He established it;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He did not create it to be empty,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but formed it to be inhabited:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I am the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and there is no other.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have not spoken in secret,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from a place in a land of darkness.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I did not say to the descendants of Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Seek Me in a wasteland.’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I, the LORD, speak the truth;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I say what is right.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Come, gather together, and draw near,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you fugitives from the nations.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Ignorant are those who carry idols of wood",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and pray to a god that cannot save.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Speak up and present your case—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yes, let them take counsel together.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Who foretold this long ago?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who announced it from ancient times?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Was it not I, the LORD?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "There is no other God but Me,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a righteous God and Savior;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there is none but Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Turn to Me and be saved,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all the ends of the earth;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for I am God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and there is no other.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "By Myself I have sworn;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "truth has gone out from My mouth,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a word that will not be revoked:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Every knee will bow before Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "every tongue will swear allegiance.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2673
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely they will say of Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘In the LORD alone are righteousness and strength.’”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "All who rage against Him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will come to Him and be put to shame.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In the LORD all descendants of Israel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be justified and will exult.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
